# Core Project Standards

- Keep a feature folder structure: `src/features/<feature>/{domain,application,infrastructure}`.
- Use interfaces at boundaries and inject dependencies (Dependency Inversion).
- Keep classes small and focused (Single Responsibility).
- Prefer composable services over inheritance-heavy designs.
- Use generics only when they improve reuse and type safety.
- Keep naming clear, intentional, and domain-aligned.
- Avoid framework lock-in in domain contracts.
